    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51693/112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>357. Peiping’s 573, November 8, noon, and 588, November 16, noon, Japanese
                    interference with employees of the National City Bank.<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d492fn82">Neither printed; they reported details of Japanese
                        pressure placed upon Chinese employees to induce them to reveal information
                        desired (811.51693/110,112).</note> Unless you perceive objection or unless
                    the National City Bank at Peiping perceives objection, in which case the Embassy
                    at Peiping is requested to inform you, it is suggested that you take up this
                    matter with the Foreign Office in such manner as you may deem appropriate.<note
                        n="83" xml:id="d492fn83">Informal representations were made at Tokyo on
                        December 1.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Peiping. Repeated to Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
